race.comment: MORLAIX (12) has been plagued by wide draws in her last couple and form is much better than it looks. Draws an ideal gate here and should enjoy a soft run off a strong pace. Won't get a better chance to break through. SIR MYKA (4) was tested in stakes class after an impressive debut win then put away again. Returned with a solid run over 1200m and looks ideally suited out in trip now. Has upside and worth following up at this level. BELLE FROM HELL (6) was a mile winner two back and then not disgraced in tougher company last time. Well placed in this line-up. URBANISE (2) led all the way when second up at Balaklava over 1300m to get off the mark. Won by a space and has upside. Among the leading hopes again.
